Please bring your laptop, headphones, and cell phone.
data.title: Election Eve Phonebank for Julie!

data.description:
So many of Julie's supporters have opened their home to her, and she needs volunteers to man the table at the event entrance to make sure we get every attendee's completed sign-in info and to answer any questions attendees have. 

These events are short, and everyone is extremely friendly and excited about helping Julie win in 2018.

Volunteers arrive 30 minutes before hand to meet, hand out Julie t-shirts to volunteers, gather materials, and go over the game plan. 

This meet and greet is being held at a private residence in Austin and we'll send details as soon as you sign up for a shift.
data.title: Volunteer for Julie at an Austin Meet and Greet!
data.summary: A great way to help Julie!

data.description:
Meeting address: 

204 S Main Street, 
Cleburne TX 76033

Time: 1:30pm - 3pm

We'll meet right on Main street in downtown Cleburne to hand out Julie t-shirts to volunteers, materials, and go over the game plan. 

The event lasts until 5pm. This should be super easy. Julie needs volunteers manning the table to make sure we're getting every attendee to sign-in and to answer any questions attendees have.

A coordinator with the campaign will be on-site to meet you, and as soon as you sign up for your shift they'll be in touch to hammer out the details!
data.title: Cleburne: Volunteer for Julie at the PDA Open House!
data.summary: A great way to spread the word about Julie with progressives from all over Johnson County

data.description:
Nothing is as effective as knocking doors and in-person conversations with folks about what is going to make things better for our state and our country. 

But if you don't live in District 25, you can still volunteer with our campaign and help Julie win, using our friend-to-friend outreach platform. 

It figures out in real time which of your contacts are registered voters in District 25, and it lets you send a warm message friend-to-friend, as opposed to using the traditional mass-email-blast outreach process.
data.title: Digital Canvassing for Julie from your laptop!
data.summary: 20 Minutes from your laptop - anywhere in the world, any time of day.

data.description:
Block-walking is the most effective way we can convince people to vote for Julie. There is no more effective way to let people know about Julie and her vision for the district than knocking doors. 

Also, it is the most fun you can have to help Julie get elected. 

We will fully train you and give you a list of houses to visit. 

These are Democrats who are EXCITED to get a knock on the door reminding them to vote--and it means a lot that they see us out there working for their vote. All you'll need is a fully charged smart phone and some comfortable shoes. We'll provide the rest. 

Grab a friend, sign up for the shift that works for you, and don't worry--you aren't expected to work the entire shift, only what you're able to commit to that day.
data.title: Cleburne: Block-walk for Julie!
data.summary: The best way to reach voters and help Julie!

data.description:
A new day really is on the horizon. Let's make sure that the women we elect in 2018 are committed to restoring our democracy! We're going to do that with good, old-fashioned person-to-person contact.

We'll meet up at campaign HQ the morning before the Women's March, distribute materials and go over the game plan, then head to the march! Let's do this!
data.title: Canvass for Julie at the Women's March!
data.summary: The best way to smash the patriarchy.

data.description:
Join the Texting Team to text directly with Julie supporters about events and volunteer opportunities.

Being a member of the Texting Team means being part of a committed group who believe Texans in District 25 - from Austin, all the way from Wimberley to Burleson - deserves a Representative that will meet with constituents and actually listen to their concerns, and who will fight to make life better for every person in the district.

We use an online program to text supporters so you don't have to worry about using your own cell phone or phone number. 
 
We identify and mobilize Julie supporters, volunteers, and voters all over the district -- helping us win in 2018. Join us!
data.title: Send Texts for Julie!
data.summary: Julie's campaign SMS tool means you can send messages to voters in the district from your computer, anywhere, anytime

data.description:
The movement to elect Jess King to Congress is growing. During the first weekend of January, over 300 people attended 16 house parties across the entire 16th district. So many people signed up to hold house parties in February that we have to go even bigger this month.

On February 18th and 19th, we’re hosting 5 big campaign events in 5 key areas. This is a place for new and old supporters to meet Jess, learn about our grassroots campaign, meet your neighbors, and get ready for massive voter outreach effort at the end of the month.

We’ll be recruiting volunteers for our Call Every Voter February Phonebank on February 24th & 25th. After the Supreme Court releases the new PA Congressional map, we’re going to call every single Democratic voter in the new district - in one weekend. You read that right. And we’re going to need to recruit a lot of volunteers to do it.

So join us in Ephrata at the Library Exploratorium, bring your friends, and get ready to build this movement even bigger.
data.title: Akron / Ephrata: Meet Jess King
data.summary: America is for all of us

data.description:
You can make calls for Jess anytime, anywhere using our digital dialer.


Pennsylvania’s new Congressional districts are finally out and I’ll be honest: it’s a tough map. There are more Republicans than Democrats in our new district, PA-11.

But if there was ever a year for a campaign like ours to win, it’s this year. If there were ever a candidate to do it, it’s Jess, who has spent her whole life fighting for working families right here in South Central Pennsylvania.

Every vote will matter in November. We need to hit the ground running at full speed. That’s why we’re going to call every single Democratic voter in our new district - in one weekend. You read that right. If we recruit 500 volunteers to do 500 phonebanking shifts, we can call every single Democratic voter in one weekend. Sign up and let's get it done.
data.title: Call Every Voter Phonebank
data.summary: We're going to call every voter in one weekend. Are you ready?
